Notebook[{
Cell["SelectPath", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"2d5ef769-7bdb-4500-9cdf-901a2bcbb10d"],

Cell["[LLM Generated]", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"8976d495-e466-4553-aa70-d8e412b4f49f"],

Cell["\<\
SelectPath[g, paths] returns one path drawn from the bundle treated as a \
finite metric space in path-space. SelectPath[g, paths, n] returns exactly n \
or $Failed; UpTo[n] returns up to n; All returns the whole pool. Options \
mirror FindPoint: \"From\" (All (default), \"Center\", \"Periphery\", \
\"MostVisited\", anchor -> spec, InfraSegment[{\[Ellipsis]}] -> spec), \
\"Distance\" (None (default), \"Max\", d, {dMin, dMax}), \"Metric\" \
(\"Hausdorff\" (default), \"Frechet\", \"MeanFrechet\"), \"MaxCliques\". \
Accepts InfraSegment and InfraRay wrappers; preserves the wrapper. Operator \
form SelectPath[g, n, opts][paths].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"83a64842-fdc4-4d98-aed5-3d76b1b05eee"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2291647a-1494-4e5c-920a-abed35ec1f7f"],

